PART III: THE MARKET (THE SCAFFOLDING)
Location: The Market of Sparks (Lower Ring)
Function: Commerce hub, black market, Alfonso's quest location

1. The Hanging City
Setup: The party takes a transit glyph (hard-light elevator) down from the courtyard.
Read Aloud:
"You step onto the glowing sigil and feel your stomach lurch as the floor drops away. You plummet through a shaft of blue light, falling for three full seconds before the descent slows.
You emerge onto a massive wooden and iron scaffolding bolted to the underside of the College pillar, hanging hundreds of feet above the crashing waves of the Sea of Ghosts.
The wind is brutal here. The protective dome above doesn't extend this far. Sea spray coats everything in a thin layer of ice.
The Market is a vertical labyrinth of hanging stalls, makeshift tents, and massive iron chains. Glowing soul gems provide lightΓÇöpurple, pink, sickly greenΓÇöcasting everything in garish neon. Frost Atronachs lumber along reinforced walkways, hauling crates.
The air smells of roasting meat, spilled alchemy reagents, ozone, and unrefined soul energy.
This is where the College's wealth is made."
GM Note: The Market is cold, chaotic, and dangerous. This is not the sanitized academic environment of the upper College.

2. Sergius Turrianus (The Arrogant Artisan) they stopped here.
Setup: Alfonso needs to find Sergius to learn Enchanting.
Location: The Soul's Anvil (the highest, most stable tier of the market).
Read Aloud:
"On the highest platform, you see a forge unlike any you've encountered. There is no fireΓÇöonly a massive stone anvil inscribed with glowing runes.
An Imperial man in fine robes strikes the anvil with a hammer. When the hammer hits, a concussive wave of sound ripples outward, making your ears pop. The metal on the anvil doesn't glow redΓÇöit sings, vibrating at a frequency that makes your teeth ache.
He's shouting at a weeping apprentice.
'You aligned the soul-matrix three degrees off true! This gem is worthless! Get out of my sight before I trap your soul in it!'"
The Interaction:
Sergius sees Alfonso approaching. He sneers.
Sergius's Dialogue:
"A Dark Elf smelling of rot and swamp water. You want to learn the highest art of the mind? Prove you even understand the vocabulary."
The Challenge: Alfonso must make a Magic Roll (Hard, -4) to intelligently discuss soul-matrix alignment theory.
Success: Sergius nods grudgingly. "You are crude, but your understanding of energetic decay is... novel."
Failure: Sergius points to the elevator. "Go back to the surface, hedge mage. Come back when you learn the difference between a geodic resonance and a standard soul-trap matrix." (Party must bribe him with 1,000 gold to try again).
The Quest (Regardless of Success):
Even if Alfonso passes, Sergius won't train him for free.
Sergius's Dialogue:
"I will teach you the binding arts. But I require a catalyst.
The quarantine has cut off my supply of Void Salts. The MiddenΓÇöthe undercity beneath usΓÇöhas an old Atronach Forge. A rogue Storm Atronach has fused with it, disrupting my Tonal Anvil.
Go down there. Kill it. Scrape the Void Salts from its corpse. Survive that, and you are my apprentice."
GM Note: This forces Alfonso into the Midden dungeon (Part V). The Void Salts are his ticket to learning Enchanting.

3. Enthir (The Fixer)
Setup: If the party needs black market goods (Black Soul Gems, poisons, stolen intel), they must visit Enthir.
Location: The Shadowed Nook (lowest tier, behind velvet curtains).
Read Aloud:
"You push through heavy velvet curtains into a dimly lit alcove. It smells of Skooma, expensive incense, and danger.
A Wood Elf in Imperial nobleman's clothing sits behind a low table, counting a stack of gold coins with meticulous precision. He looks up, smiles thinly.
'The famous Wardens. I was wondering when you'd find me. Enthir. Procurement specialist.'
He gestures to the goods laid out: Black Soul Gems, Daedra Hearts, lockpicks, poisons.
'I can get you anything. But gold is heavy and hard to hide. You look like people who have been places. I deal in leverage.'"
The Transaction:
Enthir's Merchant Preference: Gossip, Stories & Blackmail.
The party must offer him a high-level secret:
Valid Secrets:
The plague in the Stormcloak camp (Alfonso's doing)
The truth about the Jagged Crown (it didn't stay in Korvanjund)
Valerius's operations in Solitude (Orion's blackmail material)
Ancano's Dagon cult connections (if discovered)
The Reward:
If the secret is valuable, Enthir grants access to his restricted stock at 50% discount.
GM Note: Enthir is polite, transactional, and utterly ruthless. He will remember what the party tells him and may use it later.

