PART IV: THE DORMITORIES (THE SOCIAL HUB)
Location: Halls of Attainment & Countenance (Residential Spires)
Function: Rest area, quest board, social encounters

1. The Living Towers
Setup: The party enters the residential towers seeking rest or information.
Read Aloud:
"The Halls of Attainment and Countenance are twin spires flanking the courtyard. Inside, the howling wind is replaced by the warm murmur of student life.
The center of the tower is a hollow shaft filled with floating lights. Spiral ramps wind up the walls, connecting dozens of floors. Private rooms line the outer wallsΓÇöeach one a pocket dimension of personal experimentation.
The ground floor is a massive common room with fireplaces, tables, and notice boards covered in quest postings. Students argue over magical theory, scribble notes, and occasionally set things on fire by accident.
The air smells of coffee, spiced wine, and ozone."
GM Note: This is the social hub. The party can rest here (Long Rest), meet NPCs casually, and pick up minor quests.

2. The Guest Quarters
Setup: Mirabelle assigned the party rooms on the third floor.
Read Aloud:
"Your suite is surprisingly spacious. Five private bedrooms branch off a central sitting room. The beds are soft, the fireplace is enchanted to never go out, and there's even a small alchemy table and enchanting station (lower quality, no bonuses).
But something is off.
The previous occupant left in a hurry. The walls are covered in charcoal sketchesΓÇöfrantic, obsessive drawings of a massive red eye surrounded by writhing roots. Notes are scattered everywhere, scrawled in increasingly unstable handwriting.
One note reads: 'It isn't sleeping. It's hatching.'"
GM Note: The previous occupant was the "Mad Prophet" who ran into the courtyard screaming about Dagon. His notes foreshadow the Eye of Magnus plotline.

3. Meeting Nora (Option 2: The Dormitories)
Setup: If the party searches the towers for Nora (after the Arcanaeum incident), they find her here.
Location: Hiding in a storage closet on the fourth floor.
Read Aloud:
"You find her in a storage closet, huddled behind stacks of old textbooks. She's clutching the two black soul gems around her neck, rocking slightly.
When she sees you, she flinches.
'Please don't... I didn't mean to... the book was attacking, I just... I don't know how to stop it. I don't know how to not do it.'
Her voice is barely a whisper.
'They're always watching. The Masters. They think I'm a weapon. They think I'm a monster. I just want them to leave me alone.'"
The Conversation:
This is a social challenge, not a combat. The party's goal is to earn her trust.
High Guile/Empathy Approaches (Advantage):
"You saved yourself. That's not monstrous."
"We're not here to use you. We just want to understand."
"Those gems around your neckΓÇöthey're important to you, aren't they?"
Low Guile/Intimidation Approaches (Disadvantage):
"You could kill us all if you wanted. Why don't you?"
"The College is afraid of you. You should be afraid of yourself."
"Your power is wasted hiding in closets."
If They Succeed:
Nora opens up slightly.
Nora's Dialogue:
"My name is Nora. I... I had an accident when I was six. I summoned a Dremora Lord. I didn't mean to. I didn't even know what I was doing. It killed my parents. It trapped their souls in these gems."
(She holds up the black gems.)
"The College took me in. They said I had 'potential.' But I can't control it. When I'm scared, when I'm stressed, things just... happen. I summon things I can't unsummon. I open gates I can't close.
The Masters want me to take the exams. They want me to prove I can control it. But I can't. And when I fail... when I prove I'm just a broken, dangerous thing... they'll expel me. Or worse, they'll use me."
The Offer (If Treated Kindly):
"You're going into the Midden, aren't you? To the Atronach Forge?
I know the way. I hide down there sometimes. It's the only place where people don't stare at me.
I could... I could guide you. If you want."
GM Note: If the party accepts, Nora becomes a temporary companion for the Midden dungeon. She won't fight unless cornered, but her knowledge of the layout grants Advantage on navigation checks.

4. Other NPCs
J'zargo (The Rival):
Location: Common room, gambling with dice.
