The Singing Sea Puzzle - Running It Smoothly
Prep Materials:
Draw simple grid on paper OR use theater-of-mind with clear positioning
Track which floe is where ("Small Floe A is at coordinate X,Y")
Let players strategize openly (this is a logic puzzle, not a trap)
Common Player Solutions:
The Relay: One person rides floe to destination, jumps off, floe returns empty, next person repeats
The Sacrifice: Strongest/most mobile member stays behind, builds path back
The Engine: Kyboh uses gloves as propulsion (high risk, high reward)
The Summon: Alfonso's ghoul or Nora's summon acts as disposable weight
If They're Stuck:
