Kyboh's gloves vibrate more intensely ("They want to go there")
Nora (if present) suggests: "What if someone stays behind?"

Hjolmar Encounter Tips
Tone: Ancient, patient, inhuman. He's not hostileΓÇöbut he's not human. He sees mortals as raw materials or interesting experiments.
Voice: Slow, deliberate, like stones grinding together. No contractions ("Do not" not "Don't").
Body Language: Economical movement. When he moves, it's sudden and overwhelming (grabs Kyboh in one motion).
The Revelation: When he sees Kyboh is adapting to the shearing force, his attitude shifts from disgust to scientific curiosity. Kyboh is no longer a foolΓÇöhe's data.
The Surgery: Make it visceral. The gloves shattering. The raw, red hands. The sudden silence in Kyboh's head after weeks of Psychic Static.
The Quest: Hjolmar doesn't negotiate. "Do not return without it" is final. He doesn't care about Hemming, Riften, or the civil war. He cares about his craft.

